    "In the simplest on-policy RL setting, we collect trajectories τ = (s 1, a 1, r 1, s 2, a 2, r 2,.",
    ", s T) by rolling out π, and extract a dataset of state-action pairs and cumulative future returns",
    ", where the Monte Carlo return for each time step i is"
